<div class="container"><div style="width: 100%;text-align: center;"><h2 >Frequently Asked Questions<br><br></h2></div>

<p><strong>What is UniHyr?</strong></p>
<p>UniHyr is unique and first of its kind online marketplace (platform) that brings together larger number of employers and hiring consultants so that employers can get the right talent in super quick time, and helps consultants to increase their visibility and reach to potential employers.</p>
<p><strong>If I upload vacancy, will I be inundated with CV&rsquo;s?</strong></p>
<p>No, during uploading new position, there is an option of entering profile quota, which means that you will receive only that number of resume from each consultants working on that position in a week. For example, if you entered 5 in profile quota, it means that you will receive only 5 profiles in a week from each consultants.</p>
<p><strong>What is the difference between the Offered fee and Maximum Fees?</strong></p>
<p>Maximum fee is the fee at which UniHyr and client have agreed in their master contract.</p>
<p>Offered fee is the fee which is specified by each consultant as they sign up for a certain position. A lesser fee offered along with their performance by consultants would improve the visibility of their profiles at the employers end.</p>
<p><strong>How can I edit the requirement for a particular positions?</strong></p>
<p>Editi JD option is given at home against the position name. There are two ways in which you can modify the requirements, if you want to send the quick update then you can use the quick update option or else you can use the edit JD option to modify the job specification or upload a entirely new JD. Any changes you do will be sent as a notification to all the consultants who have signed up to work on that position.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Once I have received CV&rsquo;s can I approach candidate directly?</strong></p>
<p>CV submitted by consultants would not contain contact details<strong>.</strong> In order to progress with a particular candidate, you have to request to interview the candidate through UniHyr. It is in your interest to keep the recruitment process &lsquo;online&rsquo;, to ensure you are fully protected by our terms of business.</p></div>
